  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nThe documentation specifies:\r\n`Note: Web3 and its dependencies are now bundled into truffle-contract v4.0.2 or higher.`\r\n\r\nBut `new Web3()` produces error: `Uncaught ReferenceError: Web3 is not defined`\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. `<script src=\"/vendor/truffle-contract/dist/truffle-contract.min.js\"></script>`\r\n   * Without including web3. Does not have MetaMask installed\r\n2. `App.web3Provider = new Web3.providers.HttpProvider(\"http://localhost:8545\");`\r\n      `web3 = new Web3(App.web3Provider);`\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nSince truffle-contract v4.0.2 or higher includes Web3, `new Web3()` should work without issues.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\n`Uncaught ReferenceError: Web3 is not defined`\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Windows 10\r\n* Ethereum client: Ganache\r\n* Truffle version (`v5.0.29`):\r\n* node version (`v10.15.3`):\r\n* npm version (`6.4.1`):\r\n* npm list truffle-contract: `truffle-contract@4.0.28`",
